&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital Birmingham Anaesthetic Department &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Vacancy - Specialty Doctor General Anaesthetist x 2 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit up to 2 substantive Specialty Doctor General Anaesthetists to our current department of 22 whole time equivalents Consultants, 8 SAS doctors, 3 Physicians Assistants in Anaesthesia &amp; 2 rotating registrars from the Birmingham school of Anaesthesia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital is located in Birmingham and is an independent foundation trust providing high quality and multidisciplinary care for patients undergoing orthopedic, spinal (including complex spine) and oncological surgery. The Trust is a tertiary referral center for both these specialties and revision arthroplasty surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from enthusiastic and highly motivated anaesthetists to join our friendly and supportive department. The above posts have arisen due to an expansion of the Hospital with the exciting new addition of 4 new operating Theatres. It’s a great time to join one of the leading Orthopedic Hospitals within the UK and we are look forward to receiving applications from suitable qualified Doctors.&lt;/p&gt;
